<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="616" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                    <head>No. 612.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-03-13"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 13,
                            1881</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Foster</hi>, <hi rend="italic">American
                            Minister, St. Petersburg:</hi></p>
                    <p>Express to minister of foreign affairs the sentiments of sorrow with which
                        the President and the people of the United States have heard of the terrible
                        crime of which the Emperor has been the victim, and their profound sympathy
                        with the imperial family and the Russian people in their great
                        affliction.</p>
                    <closer><signed>BLAINE.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>